ms have: Wave of Heat &amp; Rain of Molten Lava.<br><br>Wave of Heat is partially resistable, and as such it will nearly always hit you... but with good resists, it will generally hit you for low numbers instead of high numbers.<br><br>Rain of Molten Lava is an all or nothing AE. With high resists, you will resist this most of the time, but when you don't resist, you get hit for the full 300, which leads people to the misconception that resists don't help.<br><br><br>But as the others said, AE damage is inconsequential, your job is to absorb melee damage which is far more than what the AE will do to ya.<br><br>Arlina <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarlinastarbright.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlina Starbright</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 10:36:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Resists</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Even if you get your resists to over 300, you are gonna get nuked for full damage by the baddies.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I would like to correct this common misleading bit of information.<br><br>Wurms in HoT have two seperate AEs. For instance, the fire wurms have: Wave of Heat &amp; Rain of Molten Lava.<br><br>Wave of Heat is partially resistable, and as such it will nearly always hit you... but with good resists, it will generally hit you for low numbers instead of high numbers.<br><br>Rain of Molten Lava is an all or nothing AE. With high resists, you will resist this most of the time, but when you don't r